-- Angola, Republic of Congo to Sign Oil Deal Today, Angop Says
-- B y   H e n r i q u e   A l m e i d a
-- 2012-07-27T10:41:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-27/angola-republic-of-congo-to-sign-oil-deal-today-angop-says.html
Angola and the Republic of Congo
will sign an agreement to jointly exploit an oil field on their
border and share profits, Agencia Angola Press said, citing
Angolan Oil Minister Jose Maria Botelho de Vasconcelos.  Botelho de Vasconcelos traveled to Congo this morning to
sign the deal after 10 years of negotiations between the two
African countries, according to the Luanda-based  news agency .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henrique Almeida in Lisbon at 
